==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nictitate
<hw>Nic"ti*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Nictate</er>.]</ety> <def>To wink; to nictate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nictitating membrane</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
thin membrane, found in many animals at the inner angle, or beneath the
lower lid, of the eye, and capable of being drawn across the eyeball;
the third eyelid; the haw.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nictitation</ent>⟦br⟧
